	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "This cognomen appears only in the Lucilian family. If, as West suggests (AJPh 49 [1928] 240-253; cf. Cichorius RS 67-70), he was the heir of the poet and a grandfather of the relative and associate of Pompey the Great, C. is a probable praenomen." .
